bot: add /lots, /mappings, /map, /unmap commands

Lets the owner manage mappings entirely from Telegram, no need to
SSH/edit CSV/import for simple cases:

- /lots: lists FunPay lots (with id) of the current account
- /mappings: lists DB mappings with status, markup, cap, label
- /map <funpay_lot_id> <ns_service_id> [markup%] [label]: upsert
- /unmap <funpay_lot_id>: disables the mapping (keeps row in DB)

Also wires the shared FunPayClient into the bot via TelegramBot ctor,
so /lots uses the live connection (no second login).
